ent.origin: Old English ule, of Germanic origin; related to Dutch uil and German Eule, from a base imitative of the bird's call.

p.def: a nocturnal bird of prey with large eyes, a facial disc, a hooked beak, and typically a loud hooting call.
p.eg: Flammulated Owls are small owls with short ear-tufts that can be held erect or flush to the head.
